<br>
As far as roleplaying, Firiona Vie has been almost better than I had hoped for. What I've discovered thus far is that RPing tends to feed on itself. AKA I will meet someone who doesn't initally emphasize RP in their playing, however as soon as I start spouting my '...duty to Tunare and my love Dyshira...' routine and other various colorful (but useless from a XPing/uber standpoint) dialog, they can't help but respond in kind.<br>
<br>
In other words, YOU (yes you!) can make Firiona Vie great! Just keep on trying.. There is more than one way to enjoy the game, and everyone has their style, so lets mix it up and see what happens. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 4:37:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I can't speak for the rest of the sexy wood elves, but it's possibly that I might find time in my busy schedule of Elf seduction for the 'Resident sex icon of Neriak'. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
