<br>
Valquiss and the others make a good point about how RPing an evil character could get you labeled as a jerk player. <br>
<br>
That's a valid point, and one thing I need to look out for. <br>
<br>
But there is one method I use to avoid this.... I normally try to 'feel out' other RPers first before I continue.  Normally if you can distinguish players who ARE willing to role play along, it's usually a given that they realize you are simply RPing an evil character, as opposed to acting like a player who is a bona fide jerk. <br>
<br>
Although my character is elitist in nature, not to mention that Discordant Evil necromancers tend to be an insular type of people.... IMHO it's not so limiting being a Dark Elf, as we do have many perceived allies whom we tolerate (if not admire). <br>
<br>
It does seem far more difficult to do this with an evil RPing Iksar.... the Iksars have it hard, because they are called on to roleplay insular xenophobes who mistrust almost anyone with soft skin.... which is more than 90% of the population of EQ servers. I can see how this makes things more difficult for them in terms of game play. I sympathize with the Iksar RPers here, I know they really have it tough. <br>
<br>
