<br>
Entirely ooc, I am Lawful Neutral as an enchanter and I think I pull that off reasonably well, even without the &quot;thees&quot; and &quot;thous&quot;.  I've never been too impressed with my own racial history as a High Elf and I would have no problem, in theory, with joining and getting to know some Tier'dal.  Might even lead me into relationships with some of the other dark races.  But I don't speak Tier'dal really well (damn, keep meaning to work on that) and it's just never happened.  Starspun is a fairly good-oriented guild (with acknowledgement to Syll, our resident bad girl) and that's probably part of the reason why also.  But this is a character direction I'd be interested in exploring eventually.<br>
<br>
So, if there are any evil types out there with a decent command of Human, Elvish, or (unlikely) Dwarvish, feel free to get in touch with me.  I'm currently season 27 and closing on clarity.  Soon, very soon.  I've heard there's a lack of enchanters among the dark races....<br>
